      "writtenOn": "2018-06-19T01:10:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "What matters is whether `newCommits` function returns any error at all, not what kind of error. Any error can be treated as transient by the `newCommits` callee because before calling `newCommits` we\u0027ve successfully fetched latest HEADs from gitiles. Hence, I explicitly wrap err as transient at the call site in line 276.\n\nDo you agree with this logical flow? If so, looking forward to suggestions for improvements in comments or code.",
      "parentUuid": "9b523b99_9d1018c7",
